title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 12 Heavy Duck Pigeon Engraved
postcontent:
Winchester Model 12 Heavy Duck Pigeon Engraved..
This Model 12 is one of the hard to find models, 1957 model Heavy Duck 3" 12 gauge with a 30 inch barrel. Also this gun is a Pigeon model that is special in its own right. Engraved model with SILVER inlays - yes SILVER not gold. The metal is very good with some marks for it has been used in the field. Original bluing. Fantastic figured Black Walnut stock and forearm, it does a few handling marks .

The Model 12 Heavy Duck was, of course, designed for 3" shells back in the '30s when standard models were for 2 3/4" shells. They had 30 or 32 inch barrels that were heaver (thicker) than standard barrels and the Full choke was special bored. These barrels have very good long range patterns. They came with plain, solid rib, and vent rib (rare) barrels. The stock had a 13 7/8" LOP, to be used with heavy duck hunting coats (cold weather hunting.

title: For Sale:  Bushmaster Carbon 15 223/5.56
postcontent:
Bushmaster’s Carbon 15 has had an interesting history, making its debut at the 2006 SHOT Show in Vegas with mixed reviews. It has a high impact polymer receiver held up, the Carbon 15 which outclasses its new no-frills competitors who do not have a Forward Bolt Assist, the C-15 is equipped with one. This M-4 type carbine also has a 16 inch standard barrel and it comes in traditional matte military finish. This variant has a full length picatinny  forward  hand guardrail . The 16 inch barrel, and all the steel components, are manganese phosphate coated for complete protection against exterior corrosion or rust. The receivers, upper and lower, are precision molded polymer for maximum lightness and strength. The upper receiver includes an integral cartridge case deflector and a last round bolt hold open feature to alert the shooter of an empty magazine. Forward bolt assist enables the operator to continue firing under the most hostile and dirty conditions; and here the Carbon 15 stands out from its similarly priced competitors. The ribbed front handguard offers increased control and heat dissipation and is molded of mil. spec. polymer thermoset composite. Buttstock is 6 position retractable C-AR / M4 type that extends the overall length from 32 1/4 inches to 36 inches. All of these features on this variant of Bushmaster’s C15M4 series makes this not only the lightest AR-15 type rifle on the market, but the best value on the market for features offered. It comes with a  two 30 shot steel magazine. Replacement price on similarly equipped rifles, if a person can even find one, is upwards of $1000.00 apiece. I am asking $750.00 for the Carbon 15 in the photos , but will accept any reasonable offer.  $40.00 for shipping.  Must be shipped to an FFL unless purchased in Arizona face-to-face.

To sweeten the offering the Bushnell mounted on the rifle comes at no extra charge.

I am sorry but this rifle is not transferable to civilians in Aurora IL, California, Chicago / Cook County IL, Connecticut, D.C., Massachusetts, Maryland, New Jersey, New York, or any jurisdiction that restricts AR15 Rifles or 30 shot magazines.
